
A customer enters an ATM to withdraw money. At that moment, the system creates multiple threads to handle different jobs at the same time.
The withdrawal thread (HIGH priority) immediately starts checking the PIN and balance because the customer is waiting. At the same time, another thread handles balance inquiry requests, and a third thread prepares the receipt generation.
Behind everything, a daemon thread runs silently, monitoring fraud patterns and logging every transaction for security. Even if no customer is actively using the ATM, this background thread keeps running.
So while the user sees a simple “withdraw cash” action, internally multiple threads are working together to complete the task safely and quickly.


When you open YouTube and click a video, one thread immediately starts playing the video (HIGH priority) so you don’t feel delay. At the same time, another thread begins buffering upcoming video data so playback stays smooth.
While you are watching, a separate thread loads comments and likes in the background, and another thread displays ads based on your interest.
Meanwhile, a daemon thread keeps updating your watch history and recommendations, even when you are not actively interacting with the app.
All these threads work together so you feel like the app is fast and seamless.

When you send a message, one thread takes responsibility for sending the message instantly (HIGH priority). Almost at the same time, another thread is ready to receive incoming messages from your contacts.
A third thread shows the “typing…” indicator while someone is replying, and another thread keeps syncing chats across devices.
In the background, a daemon thread continuously backs up your chats to the cloud, so even if your phone crashes, your data is safe.
Even though it looks like simple chatting, many threads are working together silently.

When a user searches and places an order, one thread handles product search (HIGH priority). Another thread processes cart updates and payment gateway transaction.
A third thread manages order tracking updates, while another handles inventory check in real-time.
A daemon thread continuously updates offers and recommendations in the background.

When you place an order, one thread handles order placement (HIGH priority). Another thread sends it to the restaurant system for acceptance.
A third thread processes payment confirmation, while another updates delivery tracking in real time.
A daemon thread updates menu items and offers in the background.

When a user books a ride, one thread immediately handles ride request processing (HIGH priority). Another thread finds the nearest available driver.
At the same time, a thread calculates the fare estimation, and another tracks the live location of the vehicle.
A daemon thread continuously updates traffic data in the background.
